# Installation Instructions

## Prerequisites

- Linux (Ubuntu 18.04+ recommended) or compatible OS
- NVIDIA GPU with compute capability 6.0+
- CUDA Toolkit 11.0+ (includes nvcc compiler)
- Python 3.6+ with pip (for dataset generation only)

## Setup

1. Install CUDA Toolkit:
   Follow instructions at https://developer.nvidia.com/cuda-downloads

2. Install Python dependencies (for test data generation):
   pip3 install Pillow numpy

3. Verify CUDA installation:
   nvcc --version
   nvidia-smi

## Build

   make

## Run

   ./run.sh

   Or manually:
   ./bin/gpu_dedup -v -t 0.92 <image_directory>
